
## üîß Instructions to Run

1. Clone the Repository

   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/your-username/lora-voice-tracker.git
   cd lora-voice-tracker
   ```

2. Open in Arduino IDE

   * Open `src/main.ino` in Arduino IDE.
   * Install ESP32 board support (via Preferences ‚Üí Additional Board URLs):

     ```
     https://raw.githubusercontent.com/espressif/arduino-esp32/gh-pages/package_esp32_index.json
     ```

3. Install Required Libraries

   * From Arduino Library Manager:

     * `Adafruit SSD1306`
     * `Adafruit GFX`
     * `TinyGPS++`

4. Hardware Wiring

   * ESP32 TX (GPIO17) ‚Üí LoRa RXD
   * ESP32 RX (GPIO18) ‚Üê LoRa TXD
   * OLED (SSD1306) ‚Üí SDA, SCL (default I¬≤C)
   * GPS ‚Üí second UART (pins configurable in code)
   * I2S Mic & MAX98357A ‚Üí ESP32 I2S pins
   * Push Buttons (Voice, GPS, SOS) ‚Üí GPIOs
   * RGB LEDs + Siren ‚Üí GPIOs

5. Upload Code

   * Connect ESP32-S3 via USB-C.
   * Select board: ESP32S3 Dev Module.
   * Upload to both devices with different addresses set in code (`MY_ADDR`, `PEER_ADDR`).

6. Test Prototype

   * Press **Button 1 ‚Üí Send voice/text to peer.
   * Press **Button 2 ‚Üí Request peer GPS until pressed again.
   * Press **Button 3 ‚Üí Trigger SOS (red LED + siren).
   * Messages and status show on OLED.
